        "timestamp": "2019-05-21 00:57:12.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n> \n> (1 comment)\n> \n> See comment on user story for alternative functionality bu not necessarily equivalent to this cq.\n\nThe comment about GET from the /related-to/ endpoint is very useful, but it still requires at least 2 GET calls instead of 1. Multiplied over the number of objects that need to be retrieved in some use cases, that ends up being a significant time-sink. We would still be looking for further optimisations.",
